  "texts": [
    "Then the rank of circ(d ′) over {0, 1} satisfies rank(circ(d ′)) ≥ n -1.",
    "Let C = circ(d ′) ∈ {0, 1} n×n be the circulant matrix generated by d ′ ∈ {0, 1} n, where n is a prime such that 2 is a primitive root modulo n. Suppose d ′ / ∈ {{0} n, {1} n }.",
    "Then any submatrix of C formed by selecting m ≤ n -1 rows has full row rank over {0, 1}.Proof.",
    "By Lemma 2, C = circ(d ′) has at-least rank n -1 over {0, 1}.",
    "When C has full rank, the Lemma is trivially true, so suppose that C ∈ {0, 1} n×n has rank(C) = n -1."
